Four iso-nitrogenous (35% crude protein) and iso-caloric (393 kcal/100 g) experimental diets were prepared. The basal diet containing soybean meal, fish meal, groundnut meal, wheat flour, cod liver oil, carboxymethyl cellulose (CMC), lecithin, and vitamin C. Selenium-free vitamin-mineral mixture was prepared manually for inclusion in the experimental diet. The heat-labile components were incorporated after cooking the feed ingredients (Table 1). The control diet received no Se-NP or EPA + DHA supplementation. The rest of the three experimental diets contained 0.2 mg Se-NP kg−1 diet, in mixture with EPA + DHA at 0.2, 0.4 and 0.6%. Proximate composition of four experimental diets were analyzed using AOAC method43 (Table 1). Crude protein (CP) was estimated using nitrogen content and ether extract (EE) by solvent extraction method. Ash (mineral content) was estimated by completely burning the feed overnight in a muffle furnace at 550 °C. Total carbohydrate % was calculated using the following equation:Totalcarbohydrate%=100-CP%+EE%+Ash%.\documentclass[12pt]{minimal}
